Bank of Japan Adds 3.5 Trillion Yen Through One-Day Operation

-- B y   S a b u r o   F u n a b i k i
-- 
2011-03-16T00:06:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/bank-of-japan-adds-3-5-trillion-yen-through-one-day-operation.html
The Bank of Japan added 3.5
trillion yen ($43 billion) to the financial system in a one-day
operation today to help ease liquidity.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Saburo Funabiki in  Tokyo  at 
